        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(models): keep generated secret refs out of plaintext",
        "body": "Fixes #88562.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Persist generated env-backed SecretRef provider auth as `secretref-env:<NAME>` instead of a bare env var name.\n- Resolve that marker through `process.env` at model registry request time.\n- Treat string SecretRef markers as audit-safe while still flagging unresolved object SecretRefs and true plaintext strings.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: Per-agent `models.json` generation could persist auth-profile env `keyRef` values as bare strings such as `TENSORIX_API_KEY`, which looked like plaintext to the deep security audit and produced false-positive `PLAINTEXT_FOUND` findings.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout at `/Users/andy/openclaw-88562`, branch `fix/models-json-secret-ref-88562`, commit `ff8809782a6b6d449f6cf81fcc38bf9c021efa98`.\n\nExact steps or command run on the current head:\n\n```text\nnode --import tsx --input-type=module <secretref-models-json-proof>\ngit diff --check\ngit log --format='%h %an <%ae> %s' upstream/main..HEAD\n```\n\nRedacted terminal output:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"proof_head_sha\": \"ff8809782a6b6d449f6cf81fcc38bf9c021efa98\",\n  \"marker_generation\": {\n    \"generated_provider_apiKey\": \"secretref-env:TENSORIX_API_KEY\",\n    \"equals_secretref_env_marker\": true,\n    \"equals_bare_env_var\": false\n  },\n  \"runtime_env_resolution\": {\n    \"registry_error\": null,\n    \"resolved_ok\": true,\n    \"resolved_matches_runtime_env\": true,\n    \"resolved_value\": \"<redacted>\"\n  },\n  \"audit_result\": {\n    \"status\": \"clean\",\n    \"plaintext_count\": 0,\n    \"models_json_finding_count\": 0,\n    \"models_json_plaintext_finding_count\": 0,\n    \"models_json_findings\": []\n  }\n}\nff8809782a Andy Ye <35905412+TurboTheTurtle@users.noreply.github.com> Fix models json secret ref api keys\n```\n\nObserved result on current head: A generated provider backed by an auth-profile env `keyRef` gets `apiKey: \"secretref-env:TENSORIX_API_KEY\"`, not the bare env var name. The model registry resolves that marker through `process.env.TENSORIX_API_KEY` at request time, and the security audit reports `status: \"clean\"` with zero `models.json` findings and zero `PLAINTEXT_FOUND` findings for the generated marker.\n\nWhat was not tested: The source-tree CLI wrapper requires built `dist/entry.(m)js`, so the proof invoked the patched generator, model registry, and security audit runtime directly from source rather than `node openclaw.mjs security audit --json`.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Maintainer can modify: enabled.\n",
